pc/pcp/pct - or something

Peter's Clone Tool

This is a tool similar to cp but with a number of added features like a mirror mode
(similar to rsync, but only locally), and that it understands ACLs and Extended Attributes.

USAGE

  # Dry-run, verbose, mirror-mode
  pc -n -v -M dir-a/ dir-b

	printf("  -h             Display this information\n");
	printf("  -v             Increase verbosity\n");
	printf("  -d             Increase debugging level\n");
	printf("  -n             No-update mode\n");
	printf("  -f             Force-copy mode\n");
	printf("  -i             Ignore errors and continue\n");
	printf("  -r             Recurse into subdirectories\n");
	printf("  -p             Check and preserve permission bits\n");
	printf("  -o             Check and preserve owner/group\n");
	printf("  -t             Copy if source mtime is newer\n");
	printf("  -tt            Copy if source mtime differs and reset on target\n");
	printf("  -x             Remove/replace deleted/changed objects\n");
	printf("  -u             Do not update file contents\n");
	printf("  -z             Generate zero-holed files\n");
	printf("  -A             Enable ACLs\n");
	printf("  -X             Enable Extended Attributes\n");
	printf("  -F             Enable File Flags\n");
	printf("  -FF            Enable File Flags + UF_ARCHIVE handling\n");
	printf("  -a             Archive mode (equal to -rpptttAXFF)\n");
	printf("  -M             Mirror mode (equal to -ax)\n");
	printf("  -B <size>      Set buffer size [%lu]\n", f_bufsize);
	printf("  -D <digest>    Select file digest algorithm\n");

For details, see "pc --help".

AUTHOR

